1201
01:21:12,493 --> 01:21:15,121
Your Honor, the defense
offers these photographs...

1202
01:21:15,287 --> 01:21:17,710
...as defense exhibit B, C, D, E and F.

1203
01:21:17,873 --> 01:21:21,047
How much light comes in
with no window when the door is closed?

1204
01:21:21,210 --> 01:21:24,510
- Not much.
- How long was Henri held in such a cell?

1205
01:21:24,671 --> 01:21:25,923
I don't know exactly.

1206
01:21:26,090 --> 01:21:29,594
Three years and two months.
I have the records here, if you'd like to see.

1207
01:21:29,760 --> 01:21:31,979
- That sounds right.
- Three years and two months.

1208
01:21:32,137 --> 01:21:35,812
In that time, how often was Henri Young
allowed outside for exercise?

1209
01:21:35,974 --> 01:21:40,480
Mr. Stamphill, I do not believe that
the exercise time of an inmate is relevant.

1210
01:21:40,646 --> 01:21:42,193
Well, I do. Answer the question.

1211
01:21:42,356 --> 01:21:43,403
Objection.

1212
01:21:43,565 --> 01:21:46,034
Objection overruled.
- Henri Young tried to escape.

1213
01:21:46,193 --> 01:21:49,572
Now, when a criminal escapes from prison,
he doesn't go job-hunting.

1214
01:21:49,738 --> 01:21:53,459
He robs somebody or kills somebody.
We do all we can to discourage escape.

1215
01:21:53,617 --> 01:21:57,713
In three years and two months, how often
was Henri allowed outside for exercise?

1216
01:21:57,871 --> 01:22:01,341
- I do not believe men sentenced--
- Answer the question I'm asking.

1217
01:22:01,500 --> 01:22:04,094
How often was he allowed outside
for exercise?

1218
01:22:04,253 --> 01:22:05,846
Objection. Badgering the witness.

1219
01:22:06,004 --> 01:22:07,256
Objection overruled.

1220
01:22:07,423 --> 01:22:09,801
Mr. Glenn, you will answer that question.

1221
01:22:11,176 --> 01:22:13,349
Young man, I do not recall.

1222
01:22:13,512 --> 01:22:14,889
Heh. You don't know?

1223
01:22:15,055 --> 01:22:18,025
Surely a half hour a year
isn't too difficult to recall, now, is it?

1224
01:22:18,183 --> 01:22:21,437
Mr. Stamphill, there is no place
in my courtroom for sarcasm.

1225
01:22:21,603 --> 01:22:24,903
Sorry, Your Honor. Mr. Glenn,
I have here a list with 32 names on it.

1226
01:22:25,065 --> 01:22:29,195
Now, these are all men who were prisoners
at Alcatraz during your tenure. Correct?

1227
01:22:29,361 --> 01:22:31,409
I can't remember the name
of every prisoner.

1228
01:22:31,572 --> 01:22:33,700
I have committal papers
with your signature...

1229
01:22:33,866 --> 01:22:35,539
...as well as the late Dr. Wendell Kiley.

1230
01:22:35,701 --> 01:22:38,329
We'd like this to be marked
defense exhibit G.

1231
01:22:38,495 --> 01:22:42,671
All of these men were taken off Alcatraz
in straitjackets and placed in institutions.

1232
01:22:42,833 --> 01:22:46,007
- Is that correct?
- Objection. The question is immaterial.

1233
01:22:46,170 --> 01:22:50,801
Immaterial? Your Honor, I'm saying in lay
terms that Alcatraz drives people insane.

1234
01:22:50,966 --> 01:22:52,809
It has already done so in 32 instances.

1235
01:22:52,968 --> 01:22:55,892
If not true, the witness ought to have
the opportunity to say so.

1236
01:22:56,054 --> 01:22:58,182
If it is true, it is most material...

1237
01:22:58,348 --> 01:23:01,227
and the jury ought to be privy
to that knowledge.

1238
01:23:01,393 --> 01:23:03,942
- Objection overruled.
- Thank you.

1239
01:23:04,104 --> 01:23:09,531
Now, is it not true that these men
were taken off Alcatraz in straightjackets...

1240
01:23:09,693 --> 01:23:14,073
...and placed in mental institutions and you
and Dr. Wendell Kiley signed the papers?

1241
01:23:14,239 --> 01:23:17,709
- True.
- Is it not also true that of these 32 men...

1242
01:23:17,868 --> 01:23:21,168
...28 of them had never before set foot
inside a mental institution?

1243
01:23:21,330 --> 01:23:24,004
- Ha-ha-ha. I don't know.
- I have their records if you'd like to see.

1244
01:23:24,166 --> 01:23:26,043
- Well, I'll take your word for it.
- Okay.

1245
01:23:26,210 --> 01:23:29,089
Here are men who came to Alcatraz
legally sane...

1246
01:23:29,254 --> 01:23:32,929
...were subjected to the conditions
of Alcatraz, then deemed to be insane.

1247
01:23:33,091 --> 01:23:35,093
- Is that correct?
- Yes, but you can't say...

1248
01:23:35,260 --> 01:23:36,933
...that one causes the other.

1249
01:23:37,095 --> 01:23:40,725
Well, insanity's not a virus, is it?
It's not something we're all going to catch.

1250
01:23:40,891 --> 01:23:43,519
Objection, Your Honor.
The witness is not a psychiatrist.

1251
01:23:43,685 --> 01:23:45,153
Objection sustained.

1252
01:23:45,479 --> 01:23:49,950
Mr. Stamphill, confine your questions
to areas of Mr. Glenn's expertise.

1253
01:23:50,108 --> 01:23:53,783
Very well. Mr. Glenn's expertise.
Have you ever beaten a prisoner?

1254
01:23:53,946 --> 01:23:55,198
No, that would be illegal.

1255
01:23:55,364 --> 01:23:56,866
- Not even when provoked?
- No.

1256
01:23:57,032 --> 01:24:00,332
You've never hit, kicked,
used a blackjack or straight razor?

1257
01:24:00,494 --> 01:24:03,088
You've never punched a prisoner
in your entire career?

1258
01:24:03,247 --> 01:24:05,215
- Objection, Your Honor.
- Sustained.

1259
01:24:05,374 --> 01:24:07,376
Confine yourself
to one question at a time.

1260
01:24:07,543 --> 01:24:11,923
Is it not true that you ordered two guards
to throw Henri down a steel flight of stairs?

1261
01:24:12,089 --> 01:24:14,308
That you smashed his face
with a blackjack?

1262
01:24:14,466 --> 01:24:18,061
That you took a straight razor, sliced open
his ankle, hobbling him for life?

1263
01:24:18,220 --> 01:24:19,813
That's the truth, isn't it?

1264
01:24:19,972 --> 01:24:22,566
- Objection.
- The witness has already testified...

1265
01:24:22,724 --> 01:24:24,476
...he didn't beat any prisoners.

1266
01:24:24,643 --> 01:24:28,147
Are you aware that, in a federal court
system, perjury is a crime?

1267
01:24:28,313 --> 01:24:30,156
You could spend time in prison.

1268
01:24:30,315 --> 01:24:32,317
I would remind you, young man...

1269
01:24:32,484 --> 01:24:34,486
...Henri Young is the one on trial here,
not me.

1270
01:24:34,653 --> 01:24:37,623
I am a public servant.
I am not the bad guy.

1271
01:24:37,781 --> 01:24:43,254
I will not be treated the same way as
this lying, murdering, two-time loser!

1272
01:24:43,412 --> 01:24:44,789
Silence, Mr. Glenn.

1273
01:24:44,955 --> 01:24:50,007
Mr. Stamphill, you are perilously close
to contempt of this court.

1274
01:24:50,168 --> 01:24:53,968
You will proceed with caution.
Is that understood?

1275
01:24:55,674 --> 01:24:57,676
Temper, temper.

1276
01:25:00,470 --> 01:25:02,643
Well, would you care to withdraw
any testimony?

1277
01:25:02,806 --> 01:25:06,652
You wouldn't want somebody to come along
and testify to the contrary, would you?

1278
01:25:06,977 --> 01:25:12,234
No. I would not withdraw any testimony,
no matter what Henri Young has told you.

1279
01:25:12,524 --> 01:25:16,074
I'm not talking about Henri Young.
Who would believe him?

1280
01:25:16,987 --> 01:25:19,740
Mr. Simpson, did you ever
beat this man, Henri Young?

1281
01:25:19,906 --> 01:25:21,954
Objection, Your Honor.
This has no bearing.

1282
01:25:22,117 --> 01:25:25,542
No bearing? Your Honor, beatings have
a bearing on a man's state of mind.

1283
01:25:25,704 --> 01:25:27,672
Three years of darkness has a bearing.

1284
01:25:27,831 --> 01:25:29,833
Do we need to be psychologists
to know that?

1285
01:25:30,000 --> 01:25:32,128
You know that, Your Honor.
I know you do.

1286
01:25:32,294 --> 01:25:35,093
- Objection overruled.
- Thank you, Your Honor.

1287
01:25:35,255 --> 01:25:36,302
Mr. Simpson...

1288
01:25:36,465 --> 01:25:38,718
...did you ever beat Henri Young
with a blackjack?

1289
01:25:38,884 --> 01:25:39,931
Yes.

1290
01:25:40,093 --> 01:25:42,892
Did you ever throw Henri Young
down a steel ?ight of stairs?

1291
01:25:43,055 --> 01:25:45,183
- I did.
- You were ordered to do this?

1292
01:25:45,349 --> 01:25:47,477
- Yes.
- Tell us the name of the man...

1293
01:25:47,643 --> 01:25:50,442
...who was your superior,
who ordered you to do these things.

1294
01:25:50,604 --> 01:25:52,072
- Mr. Glenn.
- Mr. Glenn.

1295
01:25:52,230 --> 01:25:55,484
- You never went to Warden Humson?
- No, sir.

1296
01:25:55,651 --> 01:25:58,905
Thank you very much. I won't ask
where you got your bruises. I know.

1297
01:25:59,071 --> 01:26:00,243
Your witness.

1298
01:26:00,405 --> 01:26:03,079
The prosecution would like to mark
for identification...

1299
01:26:03,241 --> 01:26:05,960
...the employment records
of Mr. Derek Simpson.

1300
01:26:06,119 --> 01:26:11,171
Do you recall, Mr. Simpson,
being suspended on November 4th, 1936...

1301
01:26:11,333 --> 01:26:14,712
...and again on July 6th, 1937?

1302
01:26:14,878 --> 01:26:17,006
- Yeah.
- Speak up, Mr. Simpson.

1303
01:26:17,923 --> 01:26:19,095
Yes.

1304
01:26:19,257 --> 01:26:24,309
Is it not a fact you were fired from your job
as a guard because you are a drunk?

1305
01:26:24,471 --> 01:26:26,269
- Objection.
- That's not true.

1306
01:26:26,431 --> 01:26:27,603
- Objection.
- Overruled.

1307
01:26:27,766 --> 01:26:30,895
And that Mr. Glenn would not tolerate this
in a federal prison.

1308
01:26:31,061 --> 01:26:33,689
Isn't it true, Mr. Simpson,
having cost you your job...

1309
01:26:33,855 --> 01:26:36,779
...you would say just about anything
to get even with Mr. Glenn?

1310
01:26:37,734 --> 01:26:39,111
The jury will disregard.

1311
01:26:39,277 --> 01:26:41,780
...Mr. Simpson's testimony.

1312
01:26:42,364 --> 01:26:46,619
Good afternoon. Mr. Stamphill,
Mr. Stamphill, is everything all right?

1313
01:26:57,003 --> 01:26:58,971
You son of a bitch.
- What happened?

1314
01:26:59,131 --> 01:27:01,054
You know what happened. You set me up.

1315
01:27:01,216 --> 01:27:04,345
- What are you talking about?
- You took Simpson's picture.

1316
01:27:04,511 --> 01:27:07,435
They never would have known to tear
Simpson down if you hadn't told them.

1317
01:27:07,597 --> 01:27:09,770
Are you gonna hit me now, James?

1318
01:27:09,933 --> 01:27:11,230
Go ahead.

1319
01:27:11,393 --> 01:27:14,647
It's about time you grew up
and were a man.

1320
01:27:19,192 --> 01:27:20,239
You're my brother.

1321
01:27:21,611 --> 01:27:25,661
- You had me beaten up.
- James, that was not supposed to happen.

1322
01:27:25,824 --> 01:27:28,327
Only Simpson. You walked in,
it was bad timing.

1323
01:27:28,493 --> 01:27:30,541
Bad timing?

1324
01:27:33,123 --> 01:27:34,591
I'm putting Humson on the stand.

1325
01:27:34,750 --> 01:27:37,799
Why, James?
Humson doesn't know anything!

1326
01:27:38,462 --> 01:27:42,592
Man runs three prisons. He has to know
something. Unless he's never there.

1327
01:27:47,137 --> 01:27:49,185
Son of a bitch.

1328
01:27:52,934 --> 01:27:55,904
He was never there. Never there.

1329
01:27:56,062 --> 01:27:57,530
You never saw him?

1330
01:27:57,689 --> 01:28:01,660
No. You'd hear about
him visiting, but I never saw him.

1331
01:28:02,736 --> 01:28:05,489
Now, your own brother did that to you?
Your brother did that to you?

1332
01:28:05,655 --> 01:28:08,659
Yeah.
- Jesus, rich people are weird.

1333
01:28:08,825 --> 01:28:10,372
Hey, he)'-

1334
01:28:10,535 --> 01:28:14,915
You hear DiMaggio broke Keeler's record?
Forty-five straight games.

1335
01:28:15,081 --> 01:28:17,004
Wouldn't it be great if he never stopped?

1336
01:28:17,167 --> 01:28:20,546
Dock records show when he was here.
Every trip to Alcatraz is recorded.

1337
01:28:20,712 --> 01:28:22,840
- I had to sign in that time I went.
- Hey, Jim.

1338
01:28:23,006 --> 01:28:24,724
- What?
- We friends, huh?

1339
01:28:24,883 --> 01:28:26,055
Yeah, sure.

1340
01:28:26,218 --> 01:28:29,722
Is it over? I mean, you know? Is that all?

1341
01:28:29,888 --> 01:28:32,858
Nothing more you're gonna do
with the trial, I mean?

1342
01:28:33,016 --> 01:28:35,895
- Thought you didn't care.
- No, I don't care. I don't care.

1343
01:28:36,061 --> 01:28:39,941
It's just, you know, long as you got shit
to throw at them, we can keep talking.

1344
01:28:40,106 --> 01:28:41,904
But when it's over, it's over, huh?

1345
01:28:42,067 --> 01:28:45,071
I'm not here to keep you entertained
until the executioner comes.

1346
01:28:45,237 --> 01:28:47,080
- This trial isn't just a game.
- Hey, Jim.

1347
01:28:47,239 --> 01:28:48,661
What?

1348
01:28:52,410 --> 01:28:56,335
If I was on the outside-- I mean, you know,
if there was, like, a good fairy...

1349
01:28:56,498 --> 01:29:00,002
...and she waved a wand
and I was on the outside...

1350
01:29:00,168 --> 01:29:02,796
...you and me, would we be friends then?

1351
01:29:02,963 --> 01:29:06,809
- Yes.
- No, no, no, we wouldn't.

1352
01:29:06,967 --> 01:29:10,267
You wouldn't have nothing to do with me.
You know it.

1353
01:29:10,428 --> 01:29:13,523
What I can't figure out is why, you know.

1354
01:29:13,682 --> 01:29:17,903
I mean, we both ain't got nobody else
and we're the same age, sort of.

1355
01:29:18,061 --> 01:29:21,110
And if I'd have lived in your house...

1356
01:29:21,273 --> 01:29:25,198
...and they'd have switched us
when we was babies...

1357
01:29:25,360 --> 01:29:27,954
...I could have been just like you.

1358
01:29:28,113 --> 01:29:29,865
If they stuck you down in the hole...

1359
01:29:32,075 --> 01:29:34,373
...you could be sitting here just like me...

1360
01:29:34,536 --> 01:29:39,292
...asking how come we couldn't be friends
on the outside. You ever steal 5 bucks?

1361
01:29:42,752 --> 01:29:48,509
Once, when I was a kid,
from my brother's wallet.

1362
01:29:50,051 --> 01:29:51,644
What happened?

1363
01:29:53,346 --> 01:29:56,725
He told me not to do it again.

1364
01:29:58,935 --> 01:30:02,360
Why'd they put me in that hole
for three years?

1365
01:30:03,356 --> 01:30:06,075
I could have been just like you.

1366
01:30:08,320 --> 01:30:10,948
I'd just like to ask them, you know.

1367
01:30:25,295 --> 01:30:27,138
Raise your right hand.

1368
01:30:28,131 --> 01:30:31,931
Do you swear to tell the whole truth and
nothing but the truth, so help you God?

1369
01:30:32,093 --> 01:30:33,436
So help me God.

1370
01:30:33,845 --> 01:30:35,768
You may be seated.

1371
01:30:40,518 --> 01:30:44,694
Warden Humson, in a book you wrote,
you refer to the convicts as your children.

1372
01:30:45,023 --> 01:30:49,028
That you liken your job to that of a parent,
providing for their physical needs...

1373
01:30:49,194 --> 01:30:51,037
...and molding their character.

1374
01:30:51,196 --> 01:30:53,494
Mm-hm. Yes, I wrote that.

1375
01:30:53,657 --> 01:30:58,709
I have a record of a prisoner named Johnson
who did 500 days in the lower cells.

1376
01:30:58,870 --> 01:31:01,043
The hole, the dungeon.

1377
01:31:01,206 --> 01:31:05,962
This was a 10-year period for such offenses
as not finishing all the food on his plate...

1378
01:31:06,127 --> 01:31:09,927
...having an extra pair of socks
in his cell, keeping an untidy cell.

1379
01:31:10,548 --> 01:31:14,724
Um, smuggling food from the dining room,
crumbs, in fact, to a pet lizard.

1380
01:31:14,886 --> 01:31:17,560
Is this what you mean
when you say "molding character"?

1381
01:31:17,722 --> 01:31:20,976
No, no, no. You're twisting things here.

1382
01:31:21,142 --> 01:31:26,148
The isolation cells were simply a tool
of a temporary nature...

1383
01:31:26,314 --> 01:31:30,740
...for extreme cases
within the general population.

1384
01:31:30,902 --> 01:31:35,703
Moreover, you make it sound like
the prisoner did 1500 days at one stretch...

1385
01:31:35,865 --> 01:31:37,583
...for one infraction.

1386
01:31:37,742 --> 01:31:40,040
That's not true.

1387
01:31:40,203 --> 01:31:46,085
No. Prisoners were held
for 19 days at a time.

1388
01:31:46,251 --> 01:31:47,844
- That's all.
- That's all.

1389
01:31:49,045 --> 01:31:53,095
Perhaps you can tell me why Henri Young
did over 1000 days in the dungeon?

1390
01:31:53,258 --> 01:31:55,977
Not 19 days, but 1000 days...

1391
01:31:56,136 --> 01:31:59,640
...in total darkness with only 30 minutes
of daylight a year.

1392
01:31:59,806 --> 01:32:01,683
Yes. But he tried to escape.

1393
01:32:01,850 --> 01:32:06,276
You can't compare his offense with that of
a man who smuggled food to a lizard.

1394
01:32:06,438 --> 01:32:09,612
Now, this was the first time a
sentence of three years had been imposed?

1395
01:32:09,774 --> 01:32:10,946
It wasn't a sentence.

1396
01:32:11,109 --> 01:32:14,158
It was an administrative decision
to place him there, uh...

1397
01:32:14,320 --> 01:32:17,199
...for an undetermined amount of time.

1398
01:32:17,365 --> 01:32:21,165
Why not a time limit? Doesn't that seem
a little bit inhumane? No time limit.

1399
01:32:21,327 --> 01:32:23,295
Put simply, no.

1400
01:32:24,330 --> 01:32:27,960
While we strive to prevent crime...

1401
01:32:28,126 --> 01:32:31,221
...what shall we do with the man
who has committed it, hm?

1402
01:32:31,379 --> 01:32:34,508
We aim to make him his better self.

1403
01:32:34,674 --> 01:32:36,142
His better self.

1404
01:32:36,760 --> 01:32:39,889
Well, I'm sure that Henri Young thanks you
for his better self.

1405
01:32:40,055 --> 01:32:44,151
It's a fact you simply put Henri Young
in that dungeon and forgot all about him.

1406
01:32:44,642 --> 01:32:45,985
Washed your hands of him.

1407
01:32:46,144 --> 01:32:49,694
Henri wanted me to ask you why.
Why would you do that, sir? Why?

1408
01:32:49,856 --> 01:32:52,530
- Objection, Your Honor.
- That's not true.

1409
01:32:52,692 --> 01:32:55,366
I withdraw the question.
I apologize to the jury--

1410
01:32:55,528 --> 01:32:58,577
It's not necessary that you apologize.

1411
01:32:58,740 --> 01:33:01,835
Actually, Your Honor, it is.
You see, I made a mistake.

1412
01:33:01,993 --> 01:33:05,213
Warden Humson couldn't simply
have washed his hands of Henri Young.

1413
01:33:05,371 --> 01:33:06,418
He couldn't have.

1414
01:33:06,581 --> 01:33:09,334
Because he had absolutely no idea
he was there.

1415
01:33:09,501 --> 01:33:11,595
Isn't that true, warden?
You are never there.

1416
01:33:11,753 --> 01:33:14,677
And you permit Glenn to run that prison
any way he sees fit.

1417
01:33:14,839 --> 01:33:18,594
I am there as much as I need to be.
I run three penal institutions.

1418
01:33:19,010 --> 01:33:23,060
It's impossible to know every detail
of every inmate.

1419
01:33:23,223 --> 01:33:25,100
I have the port authority records...

1420
01:33:25,266 --> 01:33:28,190
...which you signed
every time you went to Alcatraz.

1421
01:33:28,353 --> 01:33:32,529
You went seven times in '38,
five in '39, 10 in '40...

1422
01:33:32,690 --> 01:33:36,740
...and only twice so far this year. Twenty-four
day trips in three and a half years...

1423
01:33:36,903 --> 01:33:40,373
...while Henri Young was in that dungeon
over 1000 days.

1424
01:33:40,532 --> 01:33:42,910
Twenty-four out of 1000 days.

1425
01:33:43,076 --> 01:33:45,204
That's as much as you needed
to be there?

1426
01:33:45,370 --> 01:33:48,374
You knew nothing about a man
who was left to die in a dungeon...

1427
01:33:48,540 --> 01:33:51,089
...for three and a half years, did you?
Absolutely nothing.

1428
01:33:51,251 --> 01:33:55,222
In fact, you have never even met
Henri Young, have you?

1429
01:33:55,380 --> 01:33:59,385
Right now, in fact, is the first time
you have ever seen this man. Look at him.

1430
01:33:59,884 --> 01:34:02,307
That's him there. That's Henri Young.
Right there.

1431
01:34:02,470 --> 01:34:04,347
- He tried to escape.
- He tried to escape.

1432
01:34:04,514 --> 01:34:07,518
But the fact, the cold, brutal fact,
Warden Humson...

1433
01:34:07,684 --> 01:34:11,439
...is that this man, who had never,
never before in his entire life...

1434
01:34:11,604 --> 01:34:14,608
...harmed or attempted to harm
another human being, never...

1435
01:34:14,774 --> 01:34:17,072
...was now a murderer.
That is a fact, is it not?

1436
01:34:17,235 --> 01:34:19,658
- Yes. No, he tried to escape.
- It is equally a fact--

1437
01:34:19,821 --> 01:34:22,495
You can't let them get away with this.

1438
01:34:22,657 --> 01:34:24,910
If we let them get away with this,
where would we be?

1439
01:34:25,076 --> 01:34:29,206
- What? Should we let murderers roam free?
- Henri Young was not a murderer.

1440
01:34:29,372 --> 01:34:32,626
Henri Young was not a murderer
until Alcatraz got a hold of him.

1441
01:34:32,792 --> 01:34:37,389
Now, the prison runs under your guidelines,
so you created the murderer, didn't you?

1442
01:34:37,547 --> 01:34:39,265
Didn't you?

1443
01:34:40,258 --> 01:34:43,603
He tried to escape.

1444
01:34:44,762 --> 01:34:47,857
That's the thing, you see.

1445
01:34:52,854 --> 01:34:53,901
Mr. Stamphill...

1446
01:34:54,063 --> 01:34:56,782
...do you have any further questions
for this witness?

1447
01:34:57,817 --> 01:35:01,321
- No, Your Honor.
- The witness may step down.

1448
01:35:01,487 --> 01:35:03,285
But he tried to escape.

1449
01:35:04,115 --> 01:35:06,334
I'd been trained all my life for that day.

1450
01:35:06,492 --> 01:35:09,120
Control the witness, go for the kill.

1451
01:35:09,287 --> 01:35:11,915
Win, victory.

1452
01:35:12,081 --> 01:35:14,049
School prepared me well

1453
01:35:14,209 --> 01:35:16,837
My brother, he had prepared me well.

1454
01:35:17,128 --> 01:35:20,382
Years later, he and I would reconcile.

1455
01:35:20,882 --> 01:35:23,226
Family's family, you know.

1456
01:35:24,219 --> 01:35:29,100
Mary congratulated me,
but we'd already begun to drift apart.

1457
01:35:29,974 --> 01:35:33,899
When you only try to win,
you sometimes lose sight of the goal...

1458
01:35:34,395 --> 01:35:36,113
...which should have always
remained Henri.

1459
01:35:48,117 --> 01:35:50,370
No way they're gonna
send you to the gas chamber.

1460
01:35:50,536 --> 01:35:52,834
Most is second-degree murder.
Maybe manslaughter.

1461
01:35:52,997 --> 01:35:55,841
Ten years, if you get clemency,
and you'll walk.

1462
01:35:56,000 --> 01:35:59,550
- You'll have your whole life in front of you.
- Monday morning...

1463
01:35:59,712 --> 01:36:03,467
...I want you to get up to that judge
and tell him there's been a change of plan.

1464
01:36:03,633 --> 01:36:06,887
I want you to get up there
and change my plea to guilty.

1465
01:36:07,845 --> 01:36:10,815
- That's a joke, right?
- Not to me, it's not.

1466
01:36:10,974 --> 01:36:12,567
I'm not doing it.

1467
01:36:12,725 --> 01:36:16,525
What the hell have I been doing here?
Why have I been wasting my time?

1468
01:36:16,688 --> 01:36:18,986
I never thought we'd win.

1469
01:36:19,148 --> 01:36:21,071
I thought you wanted to fight.

1470
01:36:21,234 --> 01:36:24,363
I just wanted a friend.

1471
01:36:24,779 --> 01:36:28,374
- Henri, I am your friend.
- No, you're not. No, you're not.

1472
01:36:28,533 --> 01:36:30,706
It's always about you.
It's never about me.

1473
01:36:30,868 --> 01:36:32,745
You don't understand.

1474
01:36:32,912 --> 01:36:34,539
I already lost.

1475
01:36:34,706 --> 01:36:39,212
You just keep talking and talking
and talking. And you never listen.

1476
01:36:39,377 --> 01:36:42,256
You certainly don't know
what you're talking about.

1477
01:36:42,422 --> 01:36:44,971
- You just don't know what it's like.
- What what's like?

1478
01:36:45,133 --> 01:36:46,385
Alcatraz!

1479
01:36:47,552 --> 01:36:51,102
Where do you think they're gonna send me
those 10 years you're talking about?

1480
01:36:51,264 --> 01:36:53,392
They're gonna send me back to Alcatraz.

1481
01:36:53,558 --> 01:36:56,903
- Henri, when it's over, you'll be alive.
- I'm Henri.

1482
01:36:57,729 --> 01:37:00,733
I'm the one that's gotta do the time,
not you.

1483
01:37:00,898 --> 01:37:03,572
And I can't do it. I can't do it.

1484
01:37:03,735 --> 01:37:06,409
I can't, all right?

1485
01:37:07,113 --> 01:37:08,865
Listen, it's not worth it.

1486
01:37:09,407 --> 01:37:11,159
It's not worth it.

1487
01:37:11,492 --> 01:37:13,540
Nothing's worth going back there.

1488
01:37:13,703 --> 01:37:15,000
Mm-mm.

1489
01:37:17,081 --> 01:37:19,129
Sixty-seven thousand fans...

1490
01:37:19,292 --> 01:37:21,260
...at Municipal Stadium in Cleveland...

1491
01:37:21,419 --> 01:37:25,845
...watching to see if Joe DiMaggio can keep
his 56-game hitting streak alive.

1492
01:37:26,007 --> 01:37:30,308
Jim Bagby on the mound, works the count
to 1 and 1, runner on first base.

1493
01:37:30,470 --> 01:37:32,472
Here's the pitch. Joe DiMaggio swings.

1494
01:37:32,638 --> 01:37:35,061
It's a ground ball hit out to short
to Lou Boudreau.

1495
01:37:35,224 --> 01:37:38,819
He ?ips it to Ray Mack for one out.
The relay to Grimes at first...

1496
01:37:38,978 --> 01:37:41,231
...it's in time for a double play.

1497
01:37:41,397 --> 01:37:44,617
Joe DiMaggio's 56-game hitting streak
is stopped.

1498
01:37:50,323 --> 01:37:53,042
Yeah?
- Mrs. Rosetta Dial?

1499
01:38:08,883 --> 01:38:10,385
Why are we in here, Jim?

1500
01:38:10,551 --> 01:38:13,976
Maybe there are some things
worth fighting for, Henri.

1501
01:38:20,561 --> 01:38:22,154
Henri?

1502
01:38:22,563 --> 01:38:24,486
Do I know you?

1503
01:38:25,691 --> 01:38:28,820
I'm-- I'm Rosetta, Henri.

1504
01:38:30,571 --> 01:38:32,573
I'm your sister.

1505
01:38:35,993 --> 01:38:37,040
Um...

1506
01:38:39,205 --> 01:38:40,878
My, uh...

1507
01:38:41,624 --> 01:38:44,673
My baby's name is Henri.

1508
01:38:51,008 --> 01:38:52,635
You know, Mr. Stamphill says that--

1509
01:38:52,802 --> 01:38:55,601
I was...

1510
01:38:56,347 --> 01:38:58,441
...beginning to think...

1511
01:39:00,518 --> 01:39:03,021
...that you wasn't real. That I...

1512
01:39:03,855 --> 01:39:05,528
...made you up in my mind.

1513
01:39:08,943 --> 01:39:10,866
- I want you to come--
- Rosetta.

1514
01:39:12,447 --> 01:39:16,418
I want you to tell Jim that I appreciate
him bringing you down here...

1515
01:39:16,576 --> 01:39:20,376
...and knowing that you turned out okay.

1516
01:39:20,538 --> 01:39:25,009
That means a lot. I want you to tell him,
come Monday morning...

1517
01:39:25,626 --> 01:39:29,551
...he's gonna plead me guilty
just like I said.

1518
01:39:32,467 --> 01:39:37,018
I wish I wasn't so scared of them,
Rosetta.

1519
01:39:39,640 --> 01:39:41,893
I wish to God I wasn't.

1520
01:39:59,577 --> 01:40:01,830
You take care of yourself now.

1521
01:42:05,036 --> 01:42:08,040
You may call your
next witness, Mr. Stamphill.

1522
01:42:08,205 --> 01:42:10,207
Your Honor, be just a second.

1523
01:42:10,708 --> 01:42:11,755
I'm your friend.

1524
01:42:11,917 --> 01:42:14,466
On the outside,
I'd be lucky to consider you my friend.

1525
01:42:14,629 --> 01:42:16,506
Therefore, I'm not gonna kill you.

1526
01:42:16,672 --> 01:42:19,551
Are you going to call a witness
sometime today, counselor?

1527
01:42:19,717 --> 01:42:21,390
Yes, Your Honor.

1528
01:42:21,552 --> 01:42:25,147
If you wanna change your plea, you go up
there and do it. I'm not gonna do it.

1529
01:42:25,306 --> 01:42:27,559
- Plead me guilty.
- I don't think you are guilty.

1530
01:42:27,725 --> 01:42:29,443
- That doesn't matter.
- It does to me.

1531
01:42:29,602 --> 01:42:32,572
Okay, counselor, I am very close
to finding you in contempt of--

1532
01:42:32,730 --> 01:42:34,983
Your Honor, the defense calls
Mr. Henri Young.

1533
01:42:35,149 --> 01:42:36,446
No.

1534
01:42:36,609 --> 01:42:37,861
He just lost the case.

1535
01:42:38,027 --> 01:42:40,029
You wanna change your plea,
you go up there.

1536
01:42:40,196 --> 01:42:42,870
I repeat, I'm not gonna do it for you.

1537
01:42:44,617 --> 01:42:48,247
Counselor, unless--
He's coming, Your Honor.

1538
01:42:49,372 --> 01:42:50,544
Go ahead, tell them.

1539
01:42:59,799 --> 01:43:01,801
Tell them, not me.

1540
01:43:06,055 --> 01:43:08,979
- You better ask me the right questions.
- I'll ask what I want.

1541
01:43:09,141 --> 01:43:10,859
- And I'll answer what I want.
- Fine.

1542
01:43:11,018 --> 01:43:12,110
Fine.

1543
01:43:16,399 --> 01:43:19,949
Guilty, guilty, guilty.

1544
01:43:23,906 --> 01:43:27,285
Stand up. Put your hand on the Bible.

1545
01:43:29,995 --> 01:43:34,000
Do you swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth and nothing but the truth...

1546
01:43:34,166 --> 01:43:36,134
- ...so help you God?
- So help me God.

1547
01:43:36,293 --> 01:43:39,342
- State your name for the records.
- Henri Young. Henri Young.

1548
01:43:39,505 --> 01:43:41,132
Be seated.

1549
01:43:41,424 --> 01:43:42,471
Your Honor--

1550
01:43:42,633 --> 01:43:44,556
Wanna wait until I've asked a question?

1551
01:43:44,719 --> 01:43:46,847
- I haven't asked yet.
- He's trying to trick me.

1552
01:43:47,012 --> 01:43:50,642
Please instruct the witness to refrain
from speaking until I ask a question...

1553
01:43:50,808 --> 01:43:52,981
...and then just to answer
the question I ask.

1554
01:43:53,144 --> 01:43:55,693
- He's your witness, counselor.
- He won't listen to me.

1555
01:43:55,855 --> 01:43:58,734
- He trying to trick me. I just--
Silence, Mr. Young.

1556
01:43:59,567 --> 01:44:03,322
Now, here's the way it works.
Mr. Stamphill will ask you a question...

1557
01:44:03,487 --> 01:44:05,205
...and you may answer that question.

1558
01:44:05,364 --> 01:44:09,744
However, Mr. Stamphill cannot coerce you
into testifying against yourself.

1559
01:44:09,910 --> 01:44:11,583
Now, you do understand that?

1560
01:44:11,746 --> 01:44:12,918
Yeah, I just want to--

1561
01:44:13,080 --> 01:44:17,085
Did you and I have a conversation in which
you told me you wish to change your plea--?

1562
01:44:17,251 --> 01:44:22,849
Mr. Stamphill, you will wait until
I have finished instructing the witness.

1563
01:44:23,007 --> 01:44:25,430
That's okay.
That's the question I wanted him to ask.

1564
01:44:25,593 --> 01:44:27,812
It is not okay.

1565
01:44:27,970 --> 01:44:32,771
And I do not need you to tell me
what is or is not okay.

1566
01:44:33,392 --> 01:44:35,861
In this courtroom,
I am the one who decides...

1567
01:44:36,020 --> 01:44:39,024
...what is or is not okay.

1568
01:44:39,190 --> 01:44:40,863
Okay?

1569
01:44:41,066 --> 01:44:44,195
- Yes, Your Honor.
- Well, thank you very much.

1570
01:44:45,362 --> 01:44:48,036
Counselors, approach the bench.

1571
01:44:52,077 --> 01:44:54,671
Now, you wanna tell me
what the hell is going on here?

1572
01:44:54,830 --> 01:44:56,047
I'm just trying--

1573
01:44:56,207 --> 01:44:59,427
I mean, your own defendant
is looking to me to protect him from you.

1574
01:44:59,585 --> 01:45:00,677
So, what's going on?

1575
01:45:00,836 --> 01:45:03,214
I know, Your Honor,
it seems very strange but--

1576
01:45:03,380 --> 01:45:07,101
As far as I'm concerned, you're an idiot
to put him on the stand for any reason.

1577
01:45:07,259 --> 01:45:09,762
Asking your own client
to testify against himself.

1578
01:45:10,304 --> 01:45:14,025
It doesn't seem to make a lot of sense,
but the prosecution isn't objecting so--

1579
01:45:14,183 --> 01:45:15,856
No, I'm not. Let him continue.

1580
01:45:16,018 --> 01:45:17,361
Shut up.

1581
01:45:17,895 --> 01:45:19,989
- Stamphill--
- Enough damage has been done.

1582
01:45:20,147 --> 01:45:24,493
- I don't think I can mess things up any more.
- Yes, you can.

1583
01:45:24,693 --> 01:45:28,539
All right. All right.
But you're on a very short leash, Stamphill.

1584
01:45:28,697 --> 01:45:30,415
A very short leash.

1585
01:45:30,574 --> 01:45:33,453
I will throw you in jail
for contempt myself.

1586
01:45:34,495 --> 01:45:38,250
Now, let's get this goddamn show
on the road.

1587
01:45:41,293 --> 01:45:44,672
Don't let him rattle you, James.
I think you're doing a great job.

1588
01:45:46,423 --> 01:45:48,266
Mr. Young, stop playing with that.

1589
01:45:51,720 --> 01:45:56,396
Now, do you or do you not wish
to continue testifying, Mr. Young?

1590
01:45:56,559 --> 01:45:58,937
It's okay. He asked me the right question.

1591
01:45:59,770 --> 01:46:02,239
Counselor, you may proceed.

1592
01:46:05,067 --> 01:46:08,697
Mr. Young, did you and I not have
a conversation last Friday...

1593
01:46:08,863 --> 01:46:11,912
...which you told me
you wished to change your plea to guilty?

1594
01:46:12,408 --> 01:46:15,207
Yeah, yeah, yeah. That's...

1595
01:46:15,369 --> 01:46:18,213
I wanna change my plea.
That's what I told you.

1596
01:46:18,372 --> 01:46:21,876
I'm gonna ask you the single
most important question I can ask you.

1597
01:46:22,042 --> 01:46:23,919
It's what this whole trial is about.

1598
01:46:24,503 --> 01:46:26,801
Are you guilty of the murder
of Rufus McCain?

1599
01:46:26,964 --> 01:46:29,843
I wanna change my plea to guilty.
That's what I said.

1600
01:46:30,009 --> 01:46:33,309
I didn't ask what you said you wanted to do.
I asked if you are guilty.

1601
01:46:33,470 --> 01:46:35,893
Objection, Your Honor.
He's badgering the witness.

1602
01:46:36,056 --> 01:46:38,809
- He's my witness, for chrissakes.
- I'm not your nothing.

1603
01:46:38,976 --> 01:46:42,230
If the accused wants to enter
a plea of guilty, I don't know why--

1604
01:46:42,396 --> 01:46:46,902
Silence. Mr. Stamphill,
you are skating on very thin ice here.

1605
01:46:47,359 --> 01:46:50,613
Maybe, Your Honor,
but I'd like to get to the other side.

1606
01:46:52,364 --> 01:46:56,369
Very well. You may proceed,
at your own peril.

1607
01:46:56,535 --> 01:46:57,582
Thank you.

1608
01:47:01,373 --> 01:47:04,092
Let me take this one step at a time.

1609
01:47:04,835 --> 01:47:08,806
Mr. Young, we had a conversation
in which I told you...

1610
01:47:08,964 --> 01:47:12,389
...I felt with the way the trial was going,
the most you'd have to face...

1611
01:47:12,551 --> 01:47:16,055
...more than likely, would be
another 10 years. Maybe even less.

1612
01:47:16,221 --> 01:47:18,815
- You don't give a shit--
- Ten years, that's what I said.

1613
01:47:18,974 --> 01:47:20,066
Yeah, yeah, but--

1614
01:47:20,225 --> 01:47:22,899
And then did you say to me,
that you were Henri...

1615
01:47:23,062 --> 01:47:25,656
...you were the guy
who had to do the time, not me?

1616
01:47:25,814 --> 01:47:28,818
You were the one back in Alcatraz
to do those 10 years, right?

1617
01:47:28,984 --> 01:47:32,033
That's what I told you.
Why are you doing this to me?

1618
01:47:32,196 --> 01:47:36,042
Because, Mr. Young, if you change
your plea to guilty, they will execute you.

1619
01:47:36,200 --> 01:47:37,247
You will die.

1620
01:47:37,409 --> 01:47:38,535
So fucking what?

1621
01:47:38,702 --> 01:47:40,420
I'd rather die than go back there!

1622
01:47:53,676 --> 01:47:56,395
- What did you say, Mr. Young?
- I said...

1623
01:47:57,763 --> 01:48:01,563
I said I'd rather die than go back there.
Can't you understand that?

1624
01:48:02,101 --> 01:48:05,571
Why, Henri? Why do you want to die?

1625
01:48:05,854 --> 01:48:07,572
Because.

1626
01:48:08,983 --> 01:48:10,576
Because I'm...

1627
01:48:12,277 --> 01:48:14,245
I'm scared of them.

1628
01:48:14,530 --> 01:48:17,704
I'm scared to go back there. I'm scared.

1629
01:48:17,866 --> 01:48:19,709
I'm scared. I'm scared.

1630
01:48:19,868 --> 01:48:23,088
Objection. He's finished--
I haven't finished anything.

1631
01:48:23,706 --> 01:48:25,424
Henri, look at me.

1632
01:48:25,582 --> 01:48:28,131
Henri, look at me. Look at me.

1633
01:48:28,293 --> 01:48:31,888
You were right. You were right,
I was wrong. I'm sorry.

1634
01:48:32,047 --> 01:48:34,926
I'm just talking to you right now.
Not the judge or the jury.

1635
01:48:35,092 --> 01:48:37,060
If you wanna die, we'll back you up.

1636
01:48:37,219 --> 01:48:39,347
I swear to God,
I will fight these bastards...

1637
01:48:39,513 --> 01:48:41,641
...so they will never do this
to anyone again.

1638
01:48:41,807 --> 01:48:43,935
You are not gonna die for nothing.

1639
01:48:44,101 --> 01:48:46,524
The choice is yours, Henri.

1640
01:48:46,812 --> 01:48:47,938
What do you wanna do?

1641
01:48:54,153 --> 01:48:57,032
I wanna stop being afraid.

1642
01:49:04,496 --> 01:49:06,339
All right.

1643
01:49:40,657 --> 01:49:42,500
Henri Young...

1644
01:49:44,536 --> 01:49:47,289
...are you guilty of the murder
of Rufus McCain?

1645
01:50:08,644 --> 01:50:10,692
I was the weapon...

1646
01:50:11,563 --> 01:50:13,907
...but I ain't no killer.

1647
01:50:16,151 --> 01:50:18,279
They're the murderers.

1648
01:50:29,081 --> 01:50:32,460
Bailiff, you may remove the prisoner.

1649
01:50:33,418 --> 01:50:35,671
Escort the prisoner to the holding room.

1650
01:51:03,365 --> 01:51:04,992
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury...

1651
01:51:05,159 --> 01:51:07,708
you have received your instructions.

1652
01:51:07,870 --> 01:51:11,670
You may find the defendant guilty
of involuntary manslaughter...

1653
01:51:11,832 --> 01:51:15,553
...which carries with it a maximum penalty
of three years...

1654
01:51:15,711 --> 01:51:18,260
...in which case the defendant
will be remanded...

1655
01:51:18,422 --> 01:51:21,767
...to the custody of the warden
of Alcatraz.

1656
01:51:21,925 --> 01:51:26,897
Or you may find the defendant guilty
of murder in the first degree.

1657
01:51:27,055 --> 01:51:29,433
Without a recommendation for mercy...

1658
01:51:29,600 --> 01:51:33,946
...that verdict will carry with it
a sentence of death.

1659
01:52:22,444 --> 01:52:24,697
This court is now in session.

1660
01:52:25,364 --> 01:52:29,119
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury,
how do you find?

1661
01:52:29,451 --> 01:52:31,499
The defendant will rise.

1662
01:52:33,372 --> 01:52:34,498
We, the jury...

1663
01:52:34,665 --> 01:52:36,338
...find the defendant, Henri Young...

1664
01:52:36,500 --> 01:52:39,003
...not guilty of murder
in the first-degree...

1665
01:52:39,169 --> 01:52:40,842
...and guilty of involuntary manslaughter.

1666
01:52:42,172 --> 01:52:43,674
Order. Order.

1667
01:52:43,840 --> 01:52:44,887
Your Honor...

1668
01:52:45,050 --> 01:52:47,803
...we would like permission
to address the court, if possible.

1669
01:52:47,970 --> 01:52:49,313
Very well.

1670
01:52:49,471 --> 01:52:52,099
Your Honor,
we have this day signed a petition...

1671
01:52:52,266 --> 01:52:54,689
...which I would like to read to the court.

1672
01:52:55,018 --> 01:52:59,023
"We would like the following to be read
into the record of this proceeding.

1673
01:52:59,189 --> 01:53:02,944
Though we know it will have
no legal or binding effect...

1674
01:53:03,110 --> 01:53:06,159
...we'd hope that it will have
a moral effect.

1675
01:53:07,406 --> 01:53:10,501
We, the members of the jury,
recommend and request...

1676
01:53:10,659 --> 01:53:14,129
...an immediate investigation
by the proper federal authorities...

1677
01:53:14,288 --> 01:53:18,043
...of the federal penitentiary
known as Alcatraz.

1678
01:53:18,208 --> 01:53:22,509
We find this institution, its warden,
and associate warden...

1679
01:53:22,671 --> 01:53:24,469
...guilty of crimes against humanity."

1680
01:53:27,050 --> 01:53:29,553
Thank you. The jury is dismissed.

1681
01:53:29,720 --> 01:53:31,563
This trial is concluded.

1682
01:53:31,722 --> 01:53:34,726
All rise. The defendant
is remanded to the warden of Alcatraz.

1683
01:53:36,059 --> 01:53:37,527
News from San Francisco.

1684
01:53:37,686 --> 01:53:39,359
The Young trial concludes.

1685
01:53:39,521 --> 01:53:42,070
The Rock will be investigated
as Young is vindicated...

1686
01:53:42,232 --> 01:53:45,406
...by a verdict
of involuntary manslaughter.

1687
01:53:45,569 --> 01:53:47,913
As I walked out of the courtroom that day...

1688
01:53:48,280 --> 01:53:52,126
...I did not fully realize how much
Henri and I had actually accomplished.

1689
01:53:52,284 --> 01:53:54,207
It all just happened so fast.

1690
01:53:54,369 --> 01:53:57,623
Henri, Henri, I'm gonna be up to see you
as often as I can.

1691
01:53:57,789 --> 01:54:00,759
And then you can bring
that Blanche back for a second shot, huh?

1692
01:54:00,917 --> 01:54:02,669
Yeah, I'll try. See what I can do.

1693
01:54:02,836 --> 01:54:04,088
No place like home.

1694
01:54:04,254 --> 01:54:06,427
Henri, it's not over.

1695
01:54:06,590 --> 01:54:09,719
It's not over. I'm gonna appeal
to have you moved to another prison.

1696
01:54:09,885 --> 01:54:13,105
I'm gonna file motions
to have your original case reopened.

1697
01:54:13,263 --> 01:54:15,891
Henri and Jim, together again, huh?

1698
01:54:16,058 --> 01:54:18,436
That's right.
Henri and Jim, together again.

1699
01:54:19,186 --> 01:54:21,939
- Henri and Jim, together again.
- Hey, Jim.

1700
01:54:22,105 --> 01:54:26,281
I won, didn't I?
I mean, I really did something.

1701
01:54:26,443 --> 01:54:27,569
I won.

1702
01:54:28,320 --> 01:54:30,493
That's right, Henri, you won.

1703
01:54:30,906 --> 01:54:34,956
Hey, Jim, how many games
was DiMaggio's hitting streak?

1704
01:54:35,118 --> 01:54:36,620
- Fifty-four?
- No.

1705
01:54:36,787 --> 01:54:38,209
No, I got you.

1706
01:54:38,372 --> 01:54:39,715
It was 56, wasn't it?

1707
01:54:39,873 --> 01:54:41,125
Yeah. Ha-ha-ha.

1708
01:54:44,252 --> 01:54:46,471
I'll see you soon, Henri.

1709
01:54:47,005 --> 01:54:48,973
Take care of yourself.

1710
01:55:05,982 --> 01:55:08,155
The definition of victory is:

1711
01:55:08,318 --> 01:55:11,242
"Success in any contest or struggle.

1712
01:55:12,114 --> 01:55:14,617
Engagement ending in triumph."

1713
01:55:24,626 --> 01:55:28,221
That was to be the last time
I was to see Henri Young alive.

1714
01:55:29,047 --> 01:55:33,177
Before the court date was set for an appeal,
his body was found in a cell.

1715
01:55:33,969 --> 01:55:37,519
- He laid beneath a single word-

1716
01:55:38,473 --> 01:55:40,146
"Victory. "

1717
01:55:41,143 --> 01:55:44,317
Henri Young taught me
the meaning of the word.

1718
01:55:55,031 --> 01:55:58,706
He was the only man that I have known
who gave more than he asked.

1719
01:55:58,869 --> 01:56:01,668
All that he ever wanted was a friend.

1720
01:56:01,830 --> 01:56:05,880
And I will always remember him
as one of the best friends I have ever had.

1721
01:56:07,377 --> 01:56:13,384
Unlike many men that live much longer,
Henri Young did not die in vain.

1722
01:56:14,342 --> 01:56:16,936
In the end, he was not afraid.

1723
01:56:17,679 --> 01:56:20,649
He lived and he died in triumph.

1724
01:56:22,684 --> 01:56:25,028
If only we could all do that.

1725
01:56:34,196 --> 01:56:35,743
Welcome home.

1726
01:56:37,365 --> 01:56:39,413
I've missed you, Henri.

1727
01:56:44,748 --> 01:56:46,421
Mr. Glenn...

1728
01:56:47,959 --> 01:56:52,135
...you can beat me,
you can put me back in that hole...

1729
01:56:52,297 --> 01:56:53,719
...whatever you wanna do...

1730
01:56:54,883 --> 01:56:57,102
...it doesn't matter to me.

1731
01:56:58,553 --> 01:57:00,271
Action:

1732
01:57:00,722 --> 01:57:02,520
I won.

1733
01:57:03,141 --> 01:57:05,064
Reaction:

1734
01:57:05,268 --> 01:57:08,568
You can't ever take that away from me.

1735
01:57:23,161 --> 01:57:25,038
Take him to the hole.

1736
01:57:46,434 --> 01:57:50,735
Charles Dickens once said
that solitary confinement was inhumane.

1737
01:57:51,022 --> 01:57:54,276
Seven months later,
the Supreme Court agreed.

1738
01:57:54,442 --> 01:57:58,572
And as a result of the facts brought out
in the trial of The People v. Henri Young.

1739
01:57:58,738 --> 01:58:01,867
...the dungeons of Alcatraz
were closed forever.

1740
01:58:02,158 --> 01:58:06,083
Associate Warden Glenn was brought up
on charges of mistreatment.

1741
01:58:06,246 --> 01:58:10,547
He was found guilty. He would never work
in the penal system again.

1742
01:58:11,001 --> 01:58:13,754
I remained in private practice.

1743
01:58:13,920 --> 01:58:16,264
I also became a baseball fan.

1744
01:58:17,716 --> 01:58:19,559
You did it, Henri.

